  "response": "Yes, former US presidents receive lifetime Secret Service protection after leaving office. This protection was established by the Former Presidents Act of 1958. The protection applies to the president, their spouse, and their children until the children reach the age of 16. In 2013, the law was modified to limit the protection of former presidents to 10 years after they leave office, but this was later reversed, reinstating lifetime protection. The Secret Service can modify the level of protection based on specific security assessments.",
